# Copy this file to .env.local for local development, and add the same
# variables in your Vercel project (Settings -> Environment Variables) for
# production/preview deployments. These are used ONLY on the server
# (in app/api/chat/route.js) and are never sent to the browser.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pick ONE provider. You only need to fill in the API key for the provider
# you choose — the other keys can stay blank or be omitted entirely.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AI_PROVIDER=anthropic
# Options: anthropic | gemini | nvidia

# --- Anthropic (default) ----------------------------------------------------
# Get a key at https://console.anthropic.com (Settings -> API Keys)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-OWN-KEY
# Optional override, defaults to claude-sonnet-5:
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5

# --- Google Gemini -----------------------------------------------------------
# Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# GEMINI_API_KEY=REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-OWN-KEY
# Optional override, defaults to gemini-2.5-flash:
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# --- NVIDIA NIM ----------------------------------------------------------
# Get a key at https://build.nvidia.com (starts with "nvapi-")
# NVIDIA_API_KEY=nvapi-REPLACE-WITH-YOUR-OWN-KEY
# Optional override, defaults to meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:
# NVIDIA_MODEL=meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct

# Notes on provider differences:
# - Anthropic: full web search grounding (real current news/market/job data),
#   full vision support (camera capture works).
# - Gemini: has its own Google Search grounding built in — also works well
#   for current-events questions. Full vision support.
# - NVIDIA NIM: hosts open models (Llama, Mixtral, Nemotron, etc.) at very
#   competitive cost, but has NO built-in web search — it can't look up
#   real-time news, prices, or job postings, only reason from what the
#   underlying model already knows. Vision only works if you set
#   NVIDIA_MODEL to a vision-capable model like meta/llama-3.2-11b-vision-instruct.
